metatags.og:description: Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA) The Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA) is a federal law that protects the privacy of student education records. FERPA protects college students’ education records, so they remain confidential between the college and student. Information can be found in the U.S. Department of Education publication, An Eligible Student
